/**
 * Angular cli is a command line interface for angular:
 *
 * 1. ng new project-name ===> use to create new application
 * 2. ng generate ===> use to create component, services, routes and pipes
 * 3. ng server ===> use to run application
 * 4. ng help ===> use to display the help option
 *
 *
 *
 *
 */

/**
  * Available commands:
  * 1. add: Adds support for an external library to your project.
    2. analytics: Configures the gathering of Angular CLI usage metrics. See https://v8.angular.io/cli/usage-analytics-gathering.
    3. build: (b) Compiles an Angular app into an output directory named dist/ at the given output path. Must be executed from within a workspace directory.
    4. config: Retrieves or sets Angular configuration values in the angular.json file for the workspace.
    5. doc: (d) Opens the official Angular documentation (angular.io) in a browser, and searches for a given keyword.
    6. e2e: (e) Builds and serves an Angular app, then runs end-to-end tests using Protractor.
    7. generate: (g) Generates and/or modifies files based on a schematic.
    8. help: Lists available commands and their short descriptions.
    9. lint: (l) Runs linting tools on Angular app code in a given project folder.
    10. new: (n) Creates a new workspace and an initial Angular app.
    11. run: Runs an Architect target with an optional custom builder configuration defined in your project.
    12. serve: (s) Builds and serves your app, rebuilding on file changes.
    13. test: (t) Runs unit tests in a project.
    14. update: Updates your application and its dependencies. See https://update.angular.io/
    15. version: (v) Outputs Angular CLI version.
    16. xi18n: Extracts i18n messages from source code.
  */

